at to Look For\tExpected Finding\tNext Action Current thermostat\tRemove faceplate, count wires\t2-wire (R,W) or 4-wire system\tDocument configuration Boiler control panel\tLook for transformer or control voltage\t24V transformer present\tVerify power availability Zone valves\tCheck voltage rating on valves\t24V motorized valves\tConfirm low-voltage system Smart Thermostat Installation Path Path A: Standard 24V System (Most Likely) Copy Day 1: Assessment & Ordering □ Verify 24V system at boiler □ Check for C-wire availability □ Order Ecobee Premium + professional installation □ Schedule HVAC contractor visit Day 2-3: Professional Installation □ Install C-wire if needed □ Connect Ecobee to boiler controls □ Configure zone controls if applicable □ Test system operation Day 4-7: Setup & Optimization □ Configure smart sensors □ Set heating schedules □ Calibrate temperature settings □ Monitor performance Path B: 2-Wire System Upgrade (If Needed) Based on the YouTube video analysis, if you only have 2 wires: Upgrade Step\tTechnical Requirement\tExpected Cost\tProfessional Needed? Add 24V Power\tInstall transformer at boiler\t$150-300\tYes - electrical work Run New Wire\t18/4 thermostat wire\t$100-200\tYes - through walls Install Thermostat\tConnect to boiler controls\t$200-400 labor\tYes - HVAC expertise Investment & ROI Analysis Cost-Benefit Comparison Option\tTotal Investment\tAccuracy Improvement\tAnnual Energy Savings\t3-Year ROI Keep Current Nest\t$0\tMinimal\t$0\tPoor comfort Ecobee Premium + Install\t$450-600\tExcellent\t$120-250\t75-150% DIY Honeywell T9\t$280-350\tGood\t$80-180\t85-200% Energy Efficiency Optimization Hydronic System Advantages: Excellent zone control - Heat only occupied areas Thermal mass benefits - Efficient with smart scheduling No ductwork losses - Direct heat delivery efficiency Compatible with setback schedules - Unlike heat pumps Strategic Decision Framework Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_flow_diagram {\"data\":{\"nodes\":[{\"